  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_type": "isnad",
      "arabic_text": "اَلْحُسَيْنُ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ عَنْ فَضَالَةَ عَنِ اَلْحُسَيْنِ بْنِ عُثْمَانَ عَنِ اِبْنِ مُسْكَانَ عَنْ عَنْبَسَةَ بْنِ مُصْعَبٍ قَالَ",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Al-Ḥusayn ibn Saʿīd, from Faḍālah, from Al-Ḥusayn ibn ʿUthmān, from Ibn Miskān, from ʿAnbasah ibn Muṣʿab, who said:"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فِي رَجُلٍ اِحْتَلَمَ فَلَمَّا أَصْبَحَ نَظَرَ إِلَى ثَوْبِهِ فَلَمْ يَرَ بِهِ شَيْئًا قَالَ «يُصَلِّي فِيهِ».",
      "translations": {
        "en": "I said to Abī ʿAbdillāh عليه السلام concerning a man who had a wet dream, then when morning came he looked at his garment and did not see anything on it. He said: “He may perform salat (prayer) in it.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "قُلْتُ فَرَجُلٌ رَأَى فِي الْمَنَامِ أَنَّهُ اِحْتَلَمَ فَلَمَّا قَامَ وَجَدَ بَلَلًا قَلِيلًا عَلَى طَرَفِ ذَكَرِهِ قَالَ «لَيْسَ عَلَيْهِ الْغُسْلُ إِنَّ عَلِيًّا عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ كَانَ يَقُولُ: إِنَّمَا الْغُسْلُ مِنَ الْمَاءِ الْأَكْبَرِ»."
      "translations": {
        "en": "I said: Then what about a man who saw in a dream that he had a wet dream, then when he rose he found a slight moisture on the tip of his private part? He said: “Ghusl (ritual bath) is not upon him. Indeed, ʿAlī عليه السلام used to say: ‘Ghusl is only from the greater water.’”"
      }
    }
  ],
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "summary": "This hadith gives a legal ruling concerning ritual purity after a suspected wet dream. It indicates that if no trace is found on the garment, or only slight moisture is found that does not amount to the discharge requiring ghusl (ritual bath), then ghusl is not obligatory and the garment may be used for salat (prayer).",
      "seo_question": "When is ghusl (ritual bath) required after a wet dream according to Imam al-Ṣādiq عليه السلام?",
      "key_terms": {
        "اِحْتَلَمَ": "experienced a wet dream",
        "ثَوْبِهِ": "his garment or clothing",
        "يُصَلِّي": "he performs salat (prayer)",
        "بَلَلًا": "moisture or wetness",
        "الْغُسْلُ": "the ritual bath required for major ritual impurity",
        "الْمَاءِ الْأَكْبَرِ": "the greater fluid, meaning the discharge that necessitates ghusl"
      }
    }
  },
